The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 19 August is 63,540 (7,323.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 14 August, there were 2,473 new confirmed cases (285.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 07 August, there were 2,517 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 2% (44 fewer cases).
